  "meta": {
    "package": "@camunda/design-system",
    "import": "import {Dropdown} from '@camunda/design-system';",
    "docs": "# Dropdown\n\nA single-select listbox for picking one option from a fixed set. The shadcn migration target is **`Select`**, not `DropdownMenu` — `DropdownMenu` is the action-menu primitive (Carbon's `OverflowMenu` / `MenuButton`).\n\n## When to use\n\n- **Single-select from a short, fixed list** (≤ ~10 items, no search needed). Compose `<Select>` + `<SelectTrigger>` + `<SelectContent>` + `<SelectItem>`.\n- **Form fields with a known option set** — country, language, role. Use `defaultValue` for initial selection, `value` + `onValueChange` for controlled state.\n- **Grouped options** — wrap related items in `<SelectGroup>` with `<SelectLabel>`, separated by `<SelectSeparator>`.\n- **Invalid state** — set `aria-invalid` and `className=\"border-destructive focus:ring-destructive\"` on `<SelectTrigger>`; render the error message as a sibling `<p>`.\n- **Force panel above** — pass `side=\"top\"` on `<SelectContent>`.\n\n## When not to use\n\n- **Searchable / filterable selection** — use `ComboBox`.\n- **Action menu** (clickable items that fire callbacks) — use `DropdownMenu`.\n- **Multi-select** — `Select` is single-select only. Use `ComboBox` with `<ComboboxChips>`.\n- **Boolean toggle** — use `Switch` or `Checkbox`.\n- **Mutually exclusive small set displayed inline** — use `RadioGroup` or `ToggleGroup`.\n\n## Composition\n\n- `Select`'s `value` is a **string**. If your data is an array of objects, map `value={item.id}` and look the object back up via your source array — there is no `itemToString` / `itemToElement`.\n- The trigger label uses `<SelectItemText>` (text-only). For rich content in the trigger, override `<SelectValue>` with a custom render.\n- For form serialisation, add a hidden `<input type=\"hidden\" name>` synced with the value, or use a form library's `Controller`.",
    "migrationGuide": "# Dropdown — Carbon → shadcn migration guide\n\n## Naming pitfall\n\nThe word \"Dropdown\" means different things in the two libraries:\n\n- **Carbon `Dropdown`** = a single-select listbox with custom UI (closer to a `<select>`).\n- **shadcn `DropdownMenu`** = an action menu (clickable items that fire callbacks, like a context menu — closer to Carbon's `OverflowMenu`).\n\nThe right migration target for Carbon's `Dropdown` is **shadcn's `Select`**, not `DropdownMenu`. This wrapper re-exports the canonical `Select` primitive (from `select/select.shadcn.tsx`) for that reason.\n\nIf you have Carbon `OverflowMenu` / `MenuButton` usages, those map to shadcn's `DropdownMenu` — covered separately under their own wrappers.\n\n## Carbon Dropdown vs. Carbon Select\n\nA quick reminder, because the user-facing UX is similar:\n- **Carbon `Select`**: wraps a native `<select>`. Browser-styled picker on mobile, native form serialization.\n- **Carbon `Dropdown`**: wraps a Downshift-based custom listbox. Custom UI everywhere, supports rich items via `itemToElement`, no native fallback.\n\nshadcn collapses both into one primitive (`Select` = Radix custom listbox), so Carbon `Dropdown` and Carbon `Select` migrate to the same shadcn API. The distinguishing features (e.g., Carbon Dropdown's `itemToElement` for rich items) are picked up by shadcn `Select` because `<SelectItem>` accepts arbitrary children.\n\n## Structural differences\n\nCarbon's `Dropdown` is **monolithic with `items` + `itemToString` props**: pass a JS array, the component renders the listbox.\n\nshadcn's `Select` is **fully decomposed**: `<Select>` → `<SelectTrigger>` + `<SelectValue>` → `<SelectContent>` containing `<SelectItem>`s.\n\n| Concept | Carbon `Dropdown` | shadcn `Select` |\n|---|---|---|\n| Root | `<Dropdown items={…} itemToString={…} />` | `<Select>` (open + value state) |\n| Trigger / value | implicit (built-in chevron + selected label) | `<SelectTrigger><SelectValue placeholder /></SelectTrigger>` |\n| Items | `items` prop (array of objects) | `<SelectItem value={id}>{label}</SelectItem>` per option |\n| Item label extractor | `itemToString(item)` | render the label as `<SelectItem>` children |\n| Custom item rendering | `itemToElement(item)` | render rich content as `<SelectItem>` children |\n| Field label | `titleText` | external `<label>` |\n| Helper text | `helperText` | external `<p>` |\n| Invalid + error text | `invalid` + `invalidText` | `aria-invalid` on `<SelectTrigger>` + external `<p>` |\n| Warn state | `warn` + `warnText` | not modeled — render manually |\n| Hide visible label | `hideLabel` | omit `<label>` and add `aria-label` to `<SelectTrigger>` |\n| Direction | `direction=\"top\" / \"bottom\"` | `<SelectContent side=\"top\" / \"bottom\">` (passed through Radix) |\n| Auto-align (collision) | `autoAlign` | always on via Radix Positioner |\n| Type / appearance | `type=\"default\" / \"inline\"` | not modeled — restyle `<SelectTrigger>` for inline |\n| Density | `size=\"sm\" / \"md\" / \"lg\"` | not modeled — restyle via Tailwind |\n| Light variant | `light` boolean | not modeled — theme tokens |\n| Initial selection | `initialSelectedItem` | `defaultValue` |\n| Controlled | `selectedItem` + `onChange({selectedItem})` | `value` + `onValueChange(value: string)` |\n\n## Carbon features missing in shadcn\n\n- **`titleText` / `helperText` / `invalidText` / `warnText`** — Carbon ships labels and messaging on the field. shadcn forces external composition (typically with the `Field` primitive).\n- **`warn` state** — Carbon distinguishes invalid (red) from warning (amber). shadcn has only `aria-invalid`. Mimic with hand-rolled amber classes.\n- **`itemToString` / `itemToElement`** — Carbon takes complex item objects and a stringifier. shadcn `Select` works with `string` values; you map your objects yourself: `<SelectItem value={item.id}>{item.label}</SelectItem>`.\n- **`type=\"inline\"`** — Carbon's inline-label variant where the label sits beside the trigger. shadcn requires custom flexbox.\n- **`size=\"sm\" / \"md\" / \"lg\"`** — density variants. shadcn's `<SelectTrigger>` is one fixed size; restyle with Tailwind.\n- **`light` prop** — Carbon's light-on-dark treatment. shadcn relies on theme tokens.\n- **`renderSelectedItem`** — Carbon hook to re-render the trigger label. shadcn always uses the active `<SelectItem>`'s text via `<SelectItemText>` (text-only).\n- **`downshiftProps`** — Carbon exposes the underlying Downshift instance. shadcn's Radix-based primitive doesn't expose internals; for custom keyboard or open behaviour you'd reach for the Radix props directly on `<Select>` / `<SelectTrigger>` / `<SelectContent>`.\n- **Decorator slot (`decorator`)** — experimental Carbon prop for inline ai/icon decorators. No shadcn equivalent.\n- **`<DropdownSkeleton>`** — Carbon ships a skeleton variant. shadcn has none.\n- **Selection mode `selectionFeedback=\"top\" / \"fixed\" / \"top-after-reopen\"`** — Carbon controls where the selected item appears after reopening. shadcn renders items in their array order always.\n\n## shadcn features missing in Carbon\n\n- **Decomposed structure** — render the trigger, content, items wherever you want. Carbon's slot order is fixed.\n- **Group + separator primitives** — `<SelectGroup>`, `<SelectLabel>`, `<SelectSeparator>` for richer hierarchy. Carbon Dropdown supports a `<DropdownMenuItemGroup>` but it's awkward.\n- **Per-item rich content** — render icons, descriptions, badges inside `<SelectItem>` directly without `itemToElement`.\n- **`asChild`-style swap** — every sub-component accepts `asChild` (Radix slot pattern).\n- **Animation primitives** — entry/exit animations driven by `data-state` attributes.\n- **`position=\"popper\" / \"item-aligned\"`** — choose between popper-style positioning (anchored under trigger) or item-aligned (selected item aligns with trigger). Carbon's listbox always pops below.\n- **Scroll buttons** — auto-rendered `<SelectScrollUpButton>` / `<SelectScrollDownButton>` on overflow. Carbon's listbox uses native scroll only.\n\n## Behavioural differences\n\n- **Underlying primitive** — Carbon: Downshift-based custom listbox. shadcn: Radix Select (`@radix-ui/react-select`). Both are custom UIs (not native `<select>`).\n- **Form integration** — neither serialises natively; both require either a hidden `<input>` mirror or form-library integration.\n- **Keyboard** — Both support arrow keys, type-ahead, Escape. shadcn additionally exposes Radix's lifecycle callbacks.\n- **Z-index / portal** — shadcn portals to `<body>` by default; Carbon renders inline.\n\n## Migration checklist\n\n1. Replace `<Dropdown items={items} itemToString={…} titleText helperText />` with the shadcn composition (see `Default` story for the canonical shape).\n2. Move `titleText` to a sibling `<label>`, `helperText` to a sibling `<p>`, `invalidText` to a sibling `<p>` toggled by `aria-invalid`.\n3. Replace `items` + `itemToString` + `itemToElement` with explicit `{items.map((item) => <SelectItem value={item.id}>{render(item)}</SelectItem>)}`.\n4. `selectedItem` → `value`; `initialSelectedItem` → `defaultValue`. Note: Select uses a `string` value; map back to your object via your `items` array.\n5. `onChange({selectedItem})` → `onValueChange(value: string)`.\n6. For `invalid`: add `aria-invalid` + `className=\"border-destructive focus:ring-destructive\"` to `<SelectTrigger>`.\n7. For `warn`: hand-roll amber classes — no shadcn primitive.\n8. For `direction=\"top\"`: pass `side=\"top\"` to `<SelectContent>`.\n9. If you used `itemToElement` for rich items: just put rich content as children of `<SelectItem>`. The selected-value display is text-only via `<SelectItemText>`; if you need rich content in the trigger too, override `<SelectValue>` with a custom render.\n10. Drop `size`, `type`, `light` — restyle with Tailwind classes if needed.\n11. If form serialisation is needed: add `<input type=\"hidden\" name>` synced with the selected value, or wire up `react-hook-form`'s `Controller`.\n12. **Don't migrate Carbon `Dropdown` to shadcn `DropdownMenu`** — that's the action-menu primitive, mapped to Carbon's `MenuButton` / `OverflowMenu`."
  }
}
